y_1.jpg</Url><Width>350</Width><Height>350</Height><Bytes>0</Bytes><Caption /><ThumbnailUrl>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Lobby_1_thumb.jpg</ThumbnailUrl><ThumbnailWidth>60</ThumbnailWidth><ThumbnailHeight>80</ThumbnailHeight><ThumbnailBytes>0</ThumbnailBytes><PhotoType>LobbyRestaurantAndBar</PhotoType></Photo><Photo><Url>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Restaurant_2.jpg</Url><Width>350</Width><Height>293</Height><Bytes>0</Bytes><Caption /><ThumbnailUrl>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Restaurant_2_thumb.jpg</ThumbnailUrl><ThumbnailWidth>80</ThumbnailWidth><ThumbnailHeight>60</ThumbnailHeight><ThumbnailBytes>0</ThumbnailBytes><PhotoType>LobbyRestaurantAndBar</PhotoType></Photo><Photo><Url>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Swimming_Pool_1.jpg</Url><Width>360</Width><Height>239</Height><Bytes>0</Bytes><Caption /><ThumbnailUrl>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Swimming_Pool_1_thumb.jpg</ThumbnailUrl><ThumbnailWidth>80</ThumbnailWidth><ThumbnailHeight>60</ThumbnailHeight><ThumbnailBytes>0</ThumbnailBytes><PhotoType>SwimmingPool</PhotoType></Photo><Photo><Url>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Other_1.jpg</Url><Width>350</Width><Height>273</Height><Bytes>0</Bytes><Caption /><ThumbnailUrl>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Other_1_thumb.jpg</ThumbnailUrl><ThumbnailWidth>80</ThumbnailWidth><ThumbnailHeight>60</ThumbnailHeight><ThumbnailBytes>0</ThumbnailBytes><PhotoType>OtherPhotos</PhotoType></Photo><Photo><Url>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Swimming_Pool_2.jpg</Url><Width>350</Width><Height>271</Height><Bytes>0</Bytes><Caption /><ThumbnailUrl>/RXLImages/7/ARZA-92hotel_Swimming_Pool_2_thumb.jpg</ThumbnailUrl><ThumbnailWidth>80</ThumbnailWidth><ThumbnailHeight>60</ThumbnailHeight><ThumbnailBytes>0</ThumbnailBytes><PhotoType>SwimmingPool</PhotoType></Photo><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>General</Type><Text>Baja Sardinia Center is only 200 mt. away and can be easily reached. Arzachena is about 12 Km away, while Golfo Aranci and Olbia seaports are about 32 and 35 Km away. Olbia Costa Smeralda international airport is about 35 Km away. Porto Cervo is about 5 Km away.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>SurroundingArea</Type><Text>The "Grand Hotel Smeraldo Beach" stands in Baja Sardinia exactly where nature has enjoyed itself creating a setting of rare beauty.   This large accommodation structure is built on several levels that gradually drop down to the beach and the "natural seawater swimming pools", amid granite outcrops of a pastel pink colour, often smoothed by the wind that models them into strange and different shapes of unmatched beauty, such as to create unforgettable emotions.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>RoomTypes</Type><Text>The hotel sleeps 400 people in Standard, all with comforts as a Four Star Superior Hotel. Furnishings are elegant and consistent with the type found on the Costa Smeralda. Sober fabrics, often woven in Sardinia, with strong colours, but also lively. Pleasant, with a rough but authentic feel, ingenious, unique, far for showy, the elegance of simple things. Pets not allowed.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>PropertyInformation</Type><Text>The nearby village of Baja Sardinia offers: water sports, floodlit tennis courts, excursions, car rental, pedal√≤, motor boats, first-aid post, supermarkets, church, discos, restaurants and boutiques.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>DiningFacilities</Type><Text>The Smeraldo Restaurant, alongside the scenic swimming pool, is split into interlinked rooms with cool and sober decors. The Pagoda is by the side of the beach, with a barbeque located amid the granite monuments and centuries-old junipers.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>Short</Type><Text>The hotel offers lounges and scenic terraces, from where you can see Corsica, the beaches of Tahiti and Caprera and across the island of Budelli.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Sauna</Code><Text>Sauna</Text></Amenity><Amenity><C